debug-an extension to current on-line debugging techniques.wa method of on-linr assembly-language debuggingwhich greatly simplifies several of the bookkeeping tasks characteristically associated with that processhas been developed and implemented in a program for the univac m- computer at air force cambridge researchlaboratories.  with this program, an online user may insert or delete (in symbolic assembly language)any number of lines at any point of his previously assembled program in core, with the remainderof the program being relocated appropriately.cacm may, evans, t. g.darley, d. l.ca jb march ,   : pm